  "text": "In computer graphics, filtering of values requires some form of interpolation. For the task of normal map filtering, it has been proposed to fit Gaussians to normal distributions using ExpectationMaximization (E-M), and then interpolate the parameters of the Gaussians [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The E-M algorithm allows for recovery of the underlying mixture-of-Gaussians probability model giving rise to the distribution of normals. This density estimation problem is very different from our fitting of Gaussians which finds the sum of Gaussians which best fit the data. In addition, their use of the E-M algorithm to match Gaussians together only provides a one-to-one mapping while we allow for one-tomany. Figure 3 : Overview of our pipeline.",
